# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Misconceptions
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------

oak:misconception-children-confuse-national-parks-other
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Children may confuse National Parks with other protected sites."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Protected areas fall into two categories: internationally designated (Biosphere Reserves and World Heritage sites) and nationally designated (National Parks, Areas of Outstanding Natural Beauty and National Scenic Areas). Identifying these may help."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.676049Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-confusion-country-australia-continent-oceania
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Confusion between the country of Australia and the continent of Oceania."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Spend time exploring a map of Oceania and identifying the different countries and dependencies that make up this continent."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.676063Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-limited-understanding-misconceptions-stereotypes-possible
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """Limited understanding of what misconceptions and stereotypes are and the possible impacts of these."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Discuss examples of misconceptions and stereotypes that learners have encountered in their own lives."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.676092Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-pupils-assume-volcanic-eruptions-cause
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Pupils assume that all volcanic eruptions cause fatalities."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Fatalities are reduced through detection and warning systems; evacuation procedures; emergency service response, training and funding. Iceland is very well prepared for volcanic eruptions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.676106Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-difficult-pupils-appreciate-decisions-people
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """It is difficult for pupils to appreciate that decisions people make are not always freely chosen."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """To ensure pupils appreciate the significance of socio-economic factors (including income) that can limit people's choices."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.676148Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-children-believe-renewable-resources-safe
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Children may believe that renewable resources are 'safe'."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Explain that even water - a renewable natural resource - could become too polluted to use or if trees are cut down quicker than they can be replanted then that supply of wood will be exhausted."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.676169Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-limited-understanding-concept-sustainability-doesnt
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """A limited understanding of the concept of sustainability. It doesn't mean humans need to stop all activity, they need to change how they use the environment."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Sustainability doesn't mean humans need to stop all activity, they need to change how they use the environment."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.676178Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-river-thames-longest-river-uk
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "The River Thames is the longest river in the UK."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction "The River Severn is the longest river in the UK."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.678020Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-children-understand-time-periods-discussed
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Children may not understand the time periods discussed in this lesson."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """You could make a washing line timeline in the classroom with dates familiar to the children as markers then add the maps to the timeline."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.678067Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-children-familiar-tally-charts-method
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Children may not be familiar with tally charts as a method of recording."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Practise reading and writing tallies prior to the lesson would support their understanding."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.678305Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-individuals-cant-make-impact-reducing
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Individuals can't make an impact on reducing energy usage."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction "We all have a part to play in reducing energy usage."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.678426Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-flooding-causes-bad-impacts
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Flooding only causes bad impacts."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """In some parts of the world flooding can bring sediment to the soil which helps crops grow."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.678684Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-learners-less-confident-use-aerial
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """Some learners may be less confident with the use of aerial images, maps and data."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Spend additional time recapping and consolidating learners' geographical skills in using maps and other sources of information."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.678693Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-coal-gas-oil-natural-resources
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Coal, gas and oil are the only natural resources."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """There are many other natural resources, including water, food and precious stones."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.678821Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-pupils-think-deforestation-negative-impacts
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Pupils think that deforestation only has negative impacts."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction "Trees and the deforested land can provide many benefits for humans."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.678915Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-uk-grows-its-own-food
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "The UK grows most of its own food."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction "We import about 50% of the food we eat."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.680202Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-pupils-fully-appreciate-wide-range
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """Pupils may not fully appreciate the wide range of landscapes, physical features and biomes in Africa."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Spend some time exploring different countries and regions, including major cities and different types of biome."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.680248Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-uk-same-great-britain
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "The UK is the same as Great Britain"@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """The UK is short for the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland. Northern Ireland is not in Great Britain."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.680452Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-pupils-assume-slieve-donard-smallest
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Pupils assume that Slieve Donard is the smallest mountain in the UK."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Ensure that pupils know that Slieve Donard is not the smallest mountain in the UK, but it is the smallest out of the highest peaks in England, Scotland, Wales and Northern Ireland."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.680479Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-difference-exports-imports
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "the difference between exports and imports."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Exports are selling good and services to another country and imports are bringing good and services into a country from another one."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.680587Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-parts-mobile-phone-come-one
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "All the parts of a mobile phone come from one country."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction "The raw materials which go into making phones come from all around the world."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.680656Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-greenhouse-gases-come-greenhouses-caused
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """That greenhouse gases come from greenhouses or are caused by greenhouses. This often happens when pupils don't know what a greenhouse is or how it is used."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Explain what a greenhouse is, where we can find them and how they work. Greenhouses provide artificially warmer conditions to make plants grow quicker and healthier. The are often made from glass, which traps heat from the sun inside the greenhouse."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.680711Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-children-cannot-make-impact-helping
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Children cannot make an impact on helping to solve the energy problem."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Everyone, including children, can talk to other people and campaign for action to solve the energy problem."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.680784Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-planning-their-route-children-concept
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "When planning their route children may not have any concept of distance."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Use the map scale to estimate how far the route is. An average walking speed is around 12 minutes per km."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.680797Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-maritime-nations-islands
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Maritime nations have to be islands."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """The term relates to the extent to which the nation is dependent on maritime activity for its survival. For example, Singapore is not an island but is utterly dependent on maritime trade for its economy."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.681023Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-ethical-trade-aims-make-sure
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Ethical trade only aims to make sure farmers get paid enough."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Ethical trade aims to protect the environment and protect the rights of the farmers."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.681868Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-globalisation-process-countries-people-becoming
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """Globalisation is the process by which countries and people are becoming more developed."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Globalisation is the process by which countries and people are becoming more connected."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.681872Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-believing-sustainability-environment
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Believing that sustainability is only about the environment."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """It relates to the social, economic and environmental impact of a city. This lesson focuses mainly on environmental issues but a city would not be judged to be sustainable if its citizens did not have their basic economic or social needs met."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.682049Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-children-heard-ozone-layer-think
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """Children may have heard about the ozone layer and think this is the main cause of climate change."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Whilst ozone depletion and climate change are linked, it is not a major cause of climate change."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.682069Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-children-believe-waves-cause-tides
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Children may believe that waves are cause by tides."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Tides are caused by the gravitational pull of the moon . Waves are caused by wind blowing over the sea."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.682277Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-children-think-latitude-factor-influencing
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Children may think latitude is the only factor in influencing temperature."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Explain that in winter the UK is tilted away from the Sun, which means it has less influence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.682282Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-supply-chain-starts-product-processed
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "The supply chain starts from where the product is processed."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction "The supply chain starts from the extraction of the raw materials."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.682339Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-difficulty-understanding-different-causes-overlap
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Difficulty in understanding how different causes overlap to cause hunger."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """A consequence chain (see Lesson 5) could be used to investigate the potential impacts of different causes of hunger."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.682842Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-migration-tends-negative-reasons
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Migration tends to be for negative reasons."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Although the news may focus on migration due to conflict or other negative reasons, people also choose to move for positive reasons."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.687494Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-land-mixed-use-confuse-children
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """Land can be mixed use and this may confuse some children when classifying land use type."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """You could create a mixed land use category or ask children to go with the majority land use."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.688635Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-biodiversity-loss-losing-half-uks
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """Biodiversity loss is not about losing half of the UK's plants and animals, but half the variety."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """A loss of variety could be demonstrated to children using coloured cubes. Rather than taking half of each colour, remove whole colour sets."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.688640Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-animals-exist-within-biomes-native
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "That animals can only exist within the biomes they are native to."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Animals do thrive best in their natural habitats, however in countries all around the world there are zoos and animal centres that recreate natural conditions to allow animals to live and survive in a different biome or climate zone."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.688717Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-local-area-mostly-result-local
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """The local area is mostly the result of local processes, and is not really affected by global events."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Most areas have been influenced by ideas from outside. The food we eat is often grown far from the UK. The UK is a 'melting pot' of ideas."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.689221Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-everyone-around-world-easily-access
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """That everyone, all around the world, can easily access clean fresh water whenever they need it."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """In the UK, it is easy to take water for granted because it comes out of the tap. This isn't possible in all communities. In some places, water is very scarce. People may have to travel miles to reach water as they do not have taps in their homes."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.689225Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-children-used-digital-maps-confused
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """Children who have not used digital maps before may be confused by the scales used."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Spend time demonstrating the zoom function so children don't get 'lost' in their digital maps."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.689891Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-production-energy-contributing-climate-change
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "The production of all energy is contributing to climate change."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """The production of energy through burning non-renewable fossil fuels is contributing to climate change."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.690103Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-limited-understanding-farming-food-production
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """Limited understanding of how farming and food production are connected with climate change."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction "Unit 33 Lesson 7 explores food and climate change issues in more detail."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.690108Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-fossil-fuels-coal-gas-natural
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Fossil fuels (coal, gas and natural oil) are infinite."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Fossil fuels are finite - if used at the current rate, they will run out and are not sustainable."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.690848Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-children-think-net-zero-means
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Some children may think that net zero means zero carbon emissions."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Net zero actually refers to a state in which the greenhouse gases going into the atmosphere are balanced by their removal out of the atmosphere."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.691006Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-pupils-aware-national-grid-network
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """Pupils may be aware of the National Grid as the network which is used to supply electricity."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction "Explain that the National Grid for OS maps is not (quite) the same thing."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.691565Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-river-thames-one-longest-rivers
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "The River Thames is one of the longest rivers in Europe."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """The River Thames is the longest river that solely flows in England but it is much shorter than other rivers in Europe."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.691955Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-climate-zones-biomes-refer-same
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "That climate zones and biomes refer to the same places and locations."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Biomes exist within climate zones; one climate zone can contain several biomes. Climate zones are places with similar average weather patterns, biomes are places with similar animals and plants living there."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.691972Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-sustainability-environment
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Sustainability is just to do with the environment."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Sustainability takes into account the long term needs of people, the economy and the environment."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.692631Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-nature-reserves-world-heritage-sites
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Nature reserves or world heritage sites only apply to places on land."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Many coasts and underwater ecosystems are classed as Marine Protected Areas and are protected in the same way as nature reserves."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.692912Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-water-originates-pipes-taps
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "That water originates from pipes or taps."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """All water is a natural resource and originates from bodies of water such as rivers, lakes, reservoirs."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.692918Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-early-work-graphs-charts-pupils
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """In early work with graphs and charts, pupils can easily mix up the axes and try to put the values in the wrong places on graphs like climate graphs."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """On graphs that show change over time, like climate graphs, the horizontal axis shows time (months of the year on a climate graph). The vertical axes are for numerical values representing measurements (rainfall and temperature on a climate graph)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.693898Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-people-view-local-people-new
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """Some people have the view that they are local people and new arrivals are not welcome."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """In reality, everyone in the UK is descended from new arrivals into the UK from outside. Few people are linked to a place for a long period."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.694408Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-children-impression-agricultural-crops-grown
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """Children might be under the impression that all agricultural crops are grown for human consumption."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """In fact the vast majority of European cereal crop production is used to feed animals (and create biofuels, rather than feeding people."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.695136Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-migration-problem-uk-already-full
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Migration is a problem for the UK as we are already 'full'."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Without migrants, the UK's population would be shrinking and many important jobs would not be done. Migrants contribute to the UK's culture."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.695141Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-water-comes-tap-free-resource
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "That water which comes out of the tap is a free resource."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Water is a utility, just like gas and electricity. We need utilities to run our homes and do everyday tasks. The money we pay for water goes to the company that provides our water pipes, drains, sewers and recycles our water so we can use it again."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.695535Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-renewable-energy-sources-free
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Renewable energy sources are 'free'."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """There are significant costs involved in setting up and maintaining renewable sources of energy."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.695761Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-children-believe-arable-farming-involves
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Some children may believe arable farming only involves cereal crops."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Introduce market gardening which is classed as arable farming and includes growing fruit and vegetables."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.696009Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-children-struggle-understand-concept-countour
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Some children may struggle to understand the concept of countour lines."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Showing animations and models of land in 3D with contour lines marked on can help."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.696916Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-climate-change-natural-phenomenon-humans
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Climate change is a natural phenomenon that humans are not impacting."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Human actions are contributing significantly to climate change, especially through the production and consumption of energy."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.697120Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-difficulties-understanding-science-climate-change
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Difficulties in understanding the science of climate change."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """There are many resources about the causes and impacts of climate change available online."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.697225Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-children-think-lake-district-highest
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """Children may think the Lake District has the highest mountains and longest/deepest lakes in the UK."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Point out that although Scafell Pike is the tallest mountain in England, it is not as tall as Ben Nevis (tallest in the UK). Similarly, although Windermere is over 10 miles long it is not longer than many Scottish lochs."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.697229Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-rivers-fast-near-source-become
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Rivers are fast near the source and become slower as they flow downstream."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Rivers are, on average, slower in the upper course. The reason for this is due to small rivers being slowed down by friction with the bed and the banks."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.697458Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-economic-minerals-important-everyday-life
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Economic minerals are not important to everyday life."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Nearly every product we use in day-to-day life contains economic minerals that have to be mined or quarried."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.697496Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-food-grown-farms
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "All food is grown on farms."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction "Food we eat can be grown, reared or caught."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.697500Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-children-assume-photograph-black-white
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """Some children might assume any photograph in black and white is from a very long time ago."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction "Show children a black and white photo of their local settlement today."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.697682Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-stereotypes-negative-untrue
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Stereotypes are always negative and untrue."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Stereotypes usually contain an element of truth in them, and can also be positive."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.698067Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-children-believe-arable-crops-grown
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """Children may believe that all arable crops grown in the UK are required by humans for food."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction "Explain that 40% or 2/5 of the crops grown in the UK are used for animal feed."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.698073Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-coal-generates-electricity
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Coal generates the most electricity."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """All fossil fuels do generate electricity, however, it is natural gas which is the main contributor to UK electricity generation."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.698083Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-pupils-assume-warmer-summit-mountain
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """Pupils assume that it is warmer at the summit of a mountain because you are 'closer to the sun'."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """There is low pressure at altitude which means that air is thinner at the summit of a mountain. The thin air causes the cold temperatures."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.700039Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-limited-understanding-difference-unprocessed-processed
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """Limited understanding of the difference between unprocessed and processed or ultra-processed foods."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Sort some different foods into categories according to their level of processing."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.700129Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-weather-climate-same-thing
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "That weather and climate are the same thing."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Weather changes from day to day, from place to place and from one season to another. Weather refers to the conditions at any particular place or time. Climate describes the average pattern of those weather conditions over a much longer period of time"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.700710Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-mountain-area-high-land
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "A mountain is any area of high land."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """A mountain has different definitions. In the UK the height is taken to be land over 2000 ft or 610 m"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.700715Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-pupils-think-indigenous-peoples-amazon
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """Pupils think all or most Indigenous peoples in the Amazon rainforest live traditional lifestyles."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Many indigenous people in the Amazon rainforest live a modern lifestyle and have a range of jobs."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.700722Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-fully-appreciating-huge-size-diversity
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """Not fully appreciating the huge size and diversity of Asia and the variations in climate and climate zones."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Use a globe/world map to highlight the size of the continent and the wide range of latitudes it covers."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.700860Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-pupils-think-our-knowledge-amazon
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """Pupils think that our knowledge about the Amazon rainforest comes only from research."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Point out that Indigenous peoples have been living in the rainforest for thousands of years and have a lot of knowledge about it."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.701378Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-early-warning-systems-predict-earthquake
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Early warning systems can predict when an earthquake will happen."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Early warning systems cannot predict when an earthquake will happen, but can notify scientists of an imminent earthquake. This then gives families and individuals valuable seconds to prepare."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.701624Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-landscape-north-south-america-mainly
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "The landscape in North and South America is mainly the same."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction "Use lesson to emphasise the diversity of landscapes in these continents."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.701635Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-time-zones-change-travel-north
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Time zones change as we travel north to south across different latitudes."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction "Time zones change as we move east to west across different longitudes."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.701640Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-non-coniferous-woodland-ancient
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "All non-coniferous woodland is ancient."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Using historical maps we can see if deciduous woodland has been recently planted - like the National Forest in the Midlands."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.701681Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-layer-background-map-gis
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "A layer is a background map on a GIS."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """A basemap is the background map in a GIS. It shows things like countries, rivers, and roads. A layer is extra information you can add on top of the basemap, for example, where volcanoes are or how many people live in each area."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.701699Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-long-rivers-continent
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "There are long rivers on every continent."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction "There are no permanent rivers in Antarctica"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.701708Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-roads-uk-built-cars-travel
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "All roads in the UK were built for cars to travel on them."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Many of our roads were built before cars were invented. They were originally built for people walking, horses, and carts. Cars came much later, and the roads were changed over time so cars could use them safely."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.701713Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-trees-renewable-resource-cut-replanted
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """Trees are a renewable resource and can just be cut down then replanted without any negative impact."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """It can take hundreds of years for some woodland to become established with the same benefits. It is important to protect the global forests that we currently have."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.701717Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-earthquakes-occur-tectonic-plate-boundaries
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Earthquakes only occur at tectonic plate boundaries."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Earthquakes can occur anywhere in the world, but they are most commonly found at tectonic plate boundaries."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.701724Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-utc-gmt-same
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "UTC and GMT are the same."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """UTC is a time standard - an agreement to synchronise the worlds timings centres to this standard time. GMT is a time zone."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.701735Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-coniferous-forests-recently-planted
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Coniferous forests are all recently planted."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """There are some remaining ancient Caledonian pinewood forests in Scotland which are coniferous."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.701740Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-aquifers-soaking-wet-see-feel
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "That aquifers are soaking wet and we can see or feel them."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Aquifers are areas of porous rock deep underground, we can not see or feel them from the surface. Rocks, like cliff faces or outcrops that we can see are not soaking wet because the water is found far deeper within the aquifer."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.701749Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-separate-countries-separate-climate-zones
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """That separate countries must be in separate climate zones or that in each single country is part of one single climate zone."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Borders between countries have been invented by humans, they are not related to climate zones which occur naturally. Climate zones can cover many countries, and big countries like Australia can have more than one climate zone within them."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.701756Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-earthquakes-random-events
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Earthquakes are random events."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Earthquakes are not random events, but are a consequence of tectonic plate movement."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.701800Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-numerical-data-valuable-geographers-text
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Numerical data is more valuable to geographers than text data."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction "All data is valuable to geographers, providing it is fair and unbiased."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.701807Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-children-think-questionnaires-multiple-choice
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """Children may think that all questionnaires have to be multiple choice selected from given responses."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Explain that sometimes it is necessary to ask opinions in an open question so that people can submit their own ideas."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.701819Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-data-fit-pattern-identified
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Not all data may fit the pattern they have identified."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """These are called anomalies and can sometimes be explained away but individual anomalies would not disprove a pattern exists."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.701829Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-earth-significantly-closer-sun-equator
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Earth is significantly closer to the Sun at the Equator."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction "Revisit pupils’ prior learning about the Earth and space in science."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.701838Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-shocks-earthquakes-happen-once
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Shocks of earthquakes only happen once."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Large earthquakes will often have an initial shock and then be followed by a series of aftershocks as the tectonic plates settle."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.701849Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-geographers-concerned-data-shows-maximum
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Geographers are only concerned with the data that shows the maximum scores."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Geographers do often use the maximum scores to show the best option, but they also look within the data to see how some variables compare with others."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.701854Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-children-see-their-job-think
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Children may not see it as their 'job' to think about risk assessemnts."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Risk assessments conducted by children are very effective as children begin to look at their environment in a different way."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.701871Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-geographers-try-hide-things-go
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """Geographers should try to hide the things that do not go to plan in their fieldwork."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """An important part of being a geographer is to be reflective and to take opportunities to improve on your practice."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.701880Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-children-understand-concept-migration
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Children may not understand the concept of migration."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Explain that some animals move from one region or habitat to another according to the seasons."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.701885Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-explaining-something-same-describing-something
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Explaining something is the same as describing something."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Describing is saying what we see, while explaining is giving reasons for something."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.701891Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-earthquakes-their-strongest-their-epicentre
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Earthquakes are their strongest at their epicentre."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Earthquakes are felt their strongest at their epicentre as that is where humans first feel them. Earthquakes are actually their strongest at their focus point, but humans do not feel them until seismic waves have travelled through the Earth's crust."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.701905Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-tsunamis-random-events-caused-severe
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Tsunamis are random events caused by severe weather."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Tsunamis are not random events but are caused by tectonic plate movement underneath the ocean."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.701912Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-recommendations-enacted-responded-enquiry-failure
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """Recommendations might not have been enacted or responded to but the enquiry was not a failure"""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Highlight the cost of enacting changes and the restrictions on budgets and resources."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.701917Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-north-america-same-usa
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "North America is the same as USA."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Use maps to identify the different countries that make up the continent of North America."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.701924Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-solar-panels-work-shade
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Solar panels do not work in the shade."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Solar panels do work in the shade and on cloudy days but they are less efficient in these conditions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.701963Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-earthquakes-take-place-plate-boundaries
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Earthquakes always take place on plate boundaries."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Most earthquakes take place on or near plate boundaries, but some smaller earthquakes can happen away from plate boundaries."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.701970Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-children-think-results-permanent
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Children might think these results will be permanent."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """If time allowed you could repeat the fieldwork on a different day, or send groups out a different times then compare the results."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.701975Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-villages-northern-italy-same
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "All villages in northern Italy are the same."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction "Villages in northern Italy have different climates, architecture and culture."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.701979Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-geographical-questions-make-good-fieldwork
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "All geographical questions make good fieldwork enquiry questions."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Fieldwork enquiry questions have to be answerable within the practical realms of data collection. Therefore some brilliant geographical questions might not be good fieldwork enquiry questions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.701984Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-broadleaf-trees-shed-their-leaves
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "All broadleaf trees shed their leaves (are deciduous)."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Some broadleaf trees are evergreen like the native holly tree. Broadleaf just means the trees have broad, flat leaves."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.701989Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-learners-confused-difference-physical-human
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """Learners may be confused about the difference between physical and human geographical features."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Physical geography features are part of the natural world whereas human features have been created or changed by humans."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.701994Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-children-my-believe-countrys-time
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Children my believe that a country's time zone is fixed and cannot be changed."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Countries occasionally change their time zone for practical or political reasons. For example, in 2024, Kazakhstan moved from using two time zones to observing only one times zone across the whole country: UTC+5"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.701998Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-children-know-light-travels-straight
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """Children may not know that light travels in straight lines, this mans they would not understand why half of the Earth is always in darkness."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Use a globe and torch in a dark room to demonstrate that only the side of the globe facing the torch will receive light. The other half remains in darkness."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.702005Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-maps-used-help-us-find
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Maps are only used to help us find out where places are."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Maps are a brilliant tool that geographers can use to record and present information as well as use for navigation."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.702013Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-nothing-help-water-supply-problems
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "That there is nothing we can do to help with water supply problems."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Water is a precious resource everywhere in the world, in all countries. We can all do our bit by using water more carefully and encouraging other people to do the same."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.702135Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-rivers-start-sea-flow-across
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Rivers start at the sea and flow across the land."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Rivers start at their source in the mountains and flow to their mouth at the sea."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.702232Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-river-flooding-influenced-natural-factors
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """River flooding is only influenced by natural factors like the amount of rainfall."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Humans can make flooding more likely by building towns and cities and deforestation."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.702276Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-pupils-say-volcanoes-explode-rather
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Pupils will often say volcanoes 'explode' rather than erupt."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Ensure that as 'good geographers' correct vocabulary for features and processes is always used and that pupils appreciate why."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.702366Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-melting-sea-ice-contribute-rising
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "The melting of sea ice will contribute to rising sea levels."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """There are some great videos of experiments used to demonstrate that only the melting of land ice (e.g. glaciers, ice sheets on Greenland and Antarctica) will exacerbate sea level rise."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.702382Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-capital-city-countrys-largest-city
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "The capital city is always the country's largest city."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction "Use examples to explain that capital cities are chosen for various reasons."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.702387Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-pupils-think-rainforests-found-tropical
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Pupils think that rainforests are only found in tropical regions."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction "Rainforests can be found in tropical and temperate regions."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.702395Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-lesson-talks-lot-tourism-traditional
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """This lesson talks a lot about tourism and traditional occupations. Some children may believe these are the only jobs for people living in the Lake District."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Explain to pupils that although tourism is the main source of income, people also need access to other services such as healthcare and the emergency services. Therefore, there will be lots of other occupations including doctors, teachers and police."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.702400Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-journeys-start-gmt
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "All journeys start in GMT."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """This lesson only uses journeys that begin in GMT. This is to avoid any that start in the western hemisphere, cross the Prime Meridian and end in the eastern hemisphere, which are more complicated for KS2 pupils to understand using time zone maps."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.702411Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-pupils-think-cliffs-headlands-same
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """Pupils may think that cliffs and headlands are the same thing or that all cliffs are headlands."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """A headland is surrounded on three sides by water. Headlands can consist of cliffs, but cliffs can be found on coastlines that are not headlands. So it is true to say that not all cliffs are headlands, therefore cliffs and headlands are not the same."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.702423Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-food-eat-comes-uk
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "All the food we eat comes from the UK."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction "A lot of the food we eat comes from different countries."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.702437Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-pupils-think-people-living-amazon
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """Pupils think that all people living in the Amazon rainforest live in small, isolated settlements."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Use the lesson content to point out that most people in the Amazon rainforest live in a few cities such as Manaus in Brazil."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.702462Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-children-need-understand-evidence-become
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """Children need to understand that evidence can become dated - especially mapping and media evidence."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """You could present some media reports of an issue which has been resolved (e.g. a new road crossing)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.702467Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-difficulties-using-digital-mapping-tools
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Difficulties in using digital mapping tools."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction "Provide additional teaching input in the use of digital maps."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.702471Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-nobody-taking-action-protect-environment
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "That nobody is taking action to protect the environment."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Find out about ways in which people are taking action to protect the environment in learners' communities and elsewhere in the world."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.702476Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-idea-protecting-land-right-decision
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "An idea that protecting the land is always the right decision."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Sometimes protecting one stretch of coastline can have negative consequences for the coastline nearby. It may become sediment starved or impacted by higher energy waves."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.702492Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-children-think-sustainability-protecting-landscape
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """Children may think that sustainability is only about protecting the landscape and environment of the Lake District."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction "Remind children that sustainability also includes economic sustainability."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.702501Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-everyone-low-income-country-lower
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """Everyone in a low income country must have a lower income than the people in a high income country."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction "Some people in low income countries are very rich."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.702508Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-learners-struggle-make-sense-atlas
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """Learners may struggle to make sense of atlas maps which often show a lot of complex information."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Spend additional time exploring a digital atlas map as a class or group to reinforce learners’ understanding of different map conventions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.702521Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-potential-tree-planting-site-needs
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "A potential tree planting site needs to meet all of the survey requirements."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """The most suitable location will be the site which has the most points. It would be ideal to score full points on the survey but trees could still be planted if some requirements weren't met."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.702528Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-food-same-carbon-footprint
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "All food has the same carbon footprint."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Meat and dairy products have a higher carbon footprint than most fruit or vegetables."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.703528Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-tourist-go-abroad
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "To be a tourist you have to go abroad."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction "You can be a tourist abroad or in your home country."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.703544Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-children-assume-biodiversity-means-total
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Children may assume that biodiversity means the total population of a species."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction "Biodiversity is  is the variety of all living things on Earth."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.703548Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-children-believe-prevailing-wind-direction
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """Children may believe prevailing wind is the direction of wind on any particular day."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """The prevailing wind is the most frequent wind direction that a location experiences."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.703901Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-settlements-grew-industrial-revolution-because
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """All settlements grew in the industrial revolution because factories were built to provide jobs."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """There are a variety of reasons settlements grow including developing as a tourist location or market town."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.704248Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-people-stereotypes-different-places
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "People may have stereotypes about different places."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Discuss where people's stereotypes come from and emphasise the importance of using multiple sources of information to build up a more accurate picture of what a place is like."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.704315Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-pupils-think-nobody-taking-action
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Pupils think that nobody is taking action to protect the Amazon rainforest."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction "Many people around the world are taking action to protect the Amazon rainforest."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.704331Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-uk-longer-europe
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "The UK is no longer in Europe."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """The UK is located in Europe but is no longer part of the European Union (a political and economic union of 27 European countries)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.704661Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-pupils-arent-aware-different-foods
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Pupils aren't aware of where different foods come from and how they are made."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Explain that some food is grown, some comes from animals and some is manufactured or processed in factories."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.705452Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-children-assume-change-involves-places
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """Children may assume that all change involves places becoming urbanised or developed."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction "Show children examples of areas that have been re-greened."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.705481Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-climate-weather-same-thing
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Climate and weather are the same thing."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Explain that weather tells you what clothes to wear that day. Climate tells you what sort of clothes you need to have in your wardrobe."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.705523Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-wood-useful-construction-industry
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Wood is only useful for the construction industry."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction "Wood has multiple everyday and industrial uses."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.705649Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-limited-understanding-supply-chain
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Limited understanding of what a supply chain is."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Refer back to the example of commercial bread production in Lesson 1. Investigate the supply chain of other common food products."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.705960Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-pupils-think-brazil-nuts-found
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Pupils think that Brazil nuts are only found in Brazil."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Brazil nuts can be found in multiple countries in South America including Peru, Brazil, Ecuador and Colombia."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.706105Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-learners-understanding-previous-experience-geography
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """Learners’ understanding and previous experience of the geography of food may vary immensely."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Assess and build on learners’ existing knowledge and understanding. Make links to any previous learning in geography and other subjects."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.706986Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-geography-something-happens-other-parts
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """Geography is something that happens in other parts of the world not in the place where we live."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Investigate the geography in local news stories as well as stories from elsewhere in the UK and other countries."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.707908Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-cities-places-people-work
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Cities are only places where people work."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Remind students that cities are places that people live and work as cities include residential areas."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.707914Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-children-think-older-parts-place
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """Children may think that older parts of a place have not changed since they have been built."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Use the photographs and evidence from fieldwork to challenge these misconceptions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.708579Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-children-think-mountains-lake-district
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Children may think the mountains of the Lake District are volcanoes."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """The volcanoes which produces the lava and ash that fell onto the Lake District were not the mountains themselves. Volcanic rock formed as a result of nearby volcanic activity."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.708692Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-pupils-read-four-figure-grid
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Pupils often read four figure grid references the wrong way round."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Remind pupils that they find the easting first by reading along the corridor, then read the northing by going up the stairs."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.708873Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-water-enters-building-multiple-places
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """That water enters a building in multiple places, or that whenever there is a tap water enters at that point."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """All buildings have at least one stopcock. This is the only point of entry for water into a building. In the event of a flood or burst pipe, the stopcock can be turned off to stop any more water entering the building."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.709111Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-geography-something-learn-school
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Geography is only something we learn at school."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Geography is all around us. We might learn it in school, at home and in many other places."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.709431Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-lack-understanding-carbon-footprint
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Lack of understanding about what a carbon footprint is."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Provide additional teaching input about carbon footprints and their link with climate change."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.709436Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-pupils-think-new-water-formed
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Pupils may think that new water is formed by the water cycle."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """The amount of water on earth is the same as it always has been. It is constant. Water can be distributed and stored in different ways and in different places over time but new water is never added to or created by the water cycle."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.709515Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-children-require-support-generate-their
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Children may require some support to generate their own yes/no questions."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """You could play the yes/no game to get children thinking about how to elicit answers of just two words."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.709741Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-planning-round-world-cruise-children
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement """When planning a round-the-world cruise children may not understand that the western edge of the map in task A matches up to the eastern edge of the map."""@en ;
  oakcurric:correction """Use a globe to demonstrate the passage of cruise ships across the Pacific and how this relates to their world maps."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.710093Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oak:misconception-rivers-stay-exactly-same-place
  a oakcurric:Misconception ;
  oakcurric:statement "Rivers always stay in exactly the same place over time."@en ;
  oakcurric:correction "Rivers can change their course over time due to erosion."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:18.710573Z"^^xsd:dateTime .
